# Catalyst One — Enterprise Metric Single Implementation Standard

**Status:** FOUNDATION STANDARD  
**This is a permanent architectural standard.**

It applies to every screen, report, dashboard, API, AI module, chart, score, KPI, and operational insight throughout Catalyst One.

---

## Primary Principle

**Every enterprise metric must have exactly one implementation.**

All consumers must use the same shared calculation.

No business formula should ever be duplicated across the application.

---

## Scope

This standard covers every calculated business value, including but not limited to:

- Operational Health Score
- Financial Health Score
- Radar Direction / Operational Vector
- Quadrant classification and counts
- Risk / priority scores
- Conversion ratios
- Pipeline velocity / average processing time
- Productivity / performance scores
- Revenue / commission forecasts
- SLA breach / aging metrics
- Any KPI, counter, or derived insight shown to management

---

## Single Implementation Rule

For each named metric:

1. **One** derive / engine / formula module owns the calculation
2. Screens, reports, dashboards, APIs, and AI modules **import and call** that module
3. UI components **must not** re-implement the formula inline
4. Parallel “compatible” copies of the same formula are **forbidden**
5. If two surfaces show the same metric name, they **must** call the same function with the same inputs

Prefer shared paths such as:

- `src/lib/**/derive-*.ts`
- `src/lib/**/*-engine*.ts`
- Domain constants that feed a single calculator

Never copy formula bodies into React components, route handlers, or prompt/AI helpers.

---

## Forbidden Patterns

- Recalculating the same score in a dashboard **and** again in a table / tooltip / export
- Slightly different thresholds or weightings for the “same” metric on different screens
- Hardcoded percentages / magic numbers that diverge from the shared engine
- AI or briefing text inventing a metric value instead of calling the shared calculator
- API responses recomputing a metric already owned by a lib module, unless the API **is** that module’s sole entry point

---

## When Adding or Changing a Metric

1. Search for existing implementations of the metric (name, aliases, related scores)
2. If one exists — **extend or fix that implementation**; do not create a second
3. If none exists — create **one** shared module, document the formula, then wire all consumers
4. If consumers currently diverge — **consolidate** before shipping the change
5. Update module rules / docs so the canonical path is obvious

---

## Consistency Guarantee

Given the same enterprise data inputs, the same metric **must** always produce the same result — regardless of which screen, report, API, or AI surface requested it.

Any discrepancy between surfaces is a **defect**.

---

## Relationship to other standards

- Strengthens `data-integrity-analytics-standard.mdc` (accuracy, SSOT, explainability)
- Aligns with `catalyst-one-development-charter.mdc` (do not duplicate business logic)
- Complements module engines (e.g. `chanakya-radar.mdc` Operational Vector / Health Score)

When speed of delivery conflicts with single implementation, **consolidate first** — never ship a second formula to “move faster.”

---

## Definition of Done (metric / analytics change)

Before marking complete:

- [ ] Canonical calculator identified or created (exactly one)
- [ ] All new/changed consumers call that calculator
- [ ] No duplicated formula left in UI, API, or AI paths touched by the change
- [ ] Formula documented at the canonical site
- [ ] Same inputs → same outputs verified across at least two consumers when multiple exist

If a second implementation remains, the work is **not** production-ready.
